There came now another change. The mother was back again in her chamber of sorrow;
                  and undried tears were yet upon her cheeks. But she was comforted and reconciled
                  to the great affliction which had been sent for good from heaven.

"Dear Marion!" said Anna, dropping a tear upon her white transparent hand, as she
                  pressed it to her lips, a few weeks after the alarming hemorrhage just mentioned;
                  "how can you look at this event so calmly?"
